    "name": "John Baker (30)",
    "profile": "Oklahoma musician, songwriter, engineer and producer. \r\n\r\n[b]When choosing an engineer named John Baker, please also consider [a=John Baker (2)], [a=John Baker (3)], [a=John Baker (12)], [a=John Baker (18)], [a=John Baker (41)], [a=John C. Baker], [a=Jon Baker], [a=Jon Baker (2)], and [a=Jonathon Baker (2)].[/b]\r\n\r\nOriginally from Colorado, he formed the band [b]Cousin Anne[/b] at age 13. Later, he formed a second group, [b]The Envy[/b], which Baker would move with him to California. He was based out of Los Angeles from the late 1980s until 2013, when he opened an audiobook editing and directing facility in Muskogee, Oklahoma. Since 1995, he has run his own studio business, with work including music projects, audiobooks/audio dramas, and dialogue work.\r\n\r\nFrom 1988 to 1992, he formed [b]The Lumins[/b], with which an albums worth of unreleased material was recorded. This he followed by creating the band The Scavengers from 1997 to 2002. He joined the New Wave/power pop band Little Girls",
